args: (Hmm... No matter where I try diving,\nI can't find them anywhere...)
Hmm? I just felt something underfoot.\n...Wait, is this a wallet?
You haven't found a wallet in this area,\nhave you?
Your timing couldn't be better!\nI just picked one up.
That's it! That's my wallet! I can't believe\nhow on the mark your fortune-telling was!
Verica used her scrying talents\nto locate this man's lost wallet.
Well, my crystal ball didn't show me the\nwallet, but it DID show you, Celliera.
And it turned out I had found the wallet!\nGoodness, that is impressive stuff.
We're just glad you found it.
I am always happy to put my\nabilities to good use.
Wait a second... I have an idea!
Certainly. What would you like to know?
I've been attempting freediving fishing\nas a kind of underwater training.
But no matter how much I try,\nI can't locate any tasty fish.
And you want Verica to look for them\nin her crystal ball?
Yep! Oh, and don't worryâ€”I plan to\nshare my haul with everyone.
I have never tried looking for fish before, \nbut will do what I can.
Hmm... Yes, I see some pale blue fish\nswimming about contentedly...
There are a great number of bubbles,\nas if someone is swimming nearby...\nAnd also a familiar flowy swimsuit...
Julietta's wearing one of those, right?
So the fish are where Julietta is!\nBut where IS she, exactly?
It is indeed! Now it's time to swim\nlike my life depends on it...
She's really putting her heart into that!\nI can't even see her over all the splashing.
Julietta seems to have noticed as well.
Back, you fell water beast! Back, I say!
Celliera! How can you speak so frivolously\nafter the fear you just caused me?!
Heh. Sorry. But you'll get some first-rate\nfish out of it, so let's call it even.
Well then, Verica? Where's my next\nfishing spot going to be located?
If I want to feed everyone, I'm going to\nneed a lot more fish than this.
Besides, I'm enjoying myself! As I chase\nfish through the water, I can just FEEL\nmy cardiopulmonary function improving!
In that case, let me see...
Look at all the fish I caught!
I owe it all to Verica's fortune-telling.\nMany thanks, my good lady!
Hee hee. You are most welcome.
Now I want to catch something massive\nso we can end this day with a bang.
Let me see if I can find anything near\nhere which matches that description.
Hmm... I see the wreckage of a ship\nand the shadow of a large fish...
Hey, I know where that shipwreck is!\nLET'S DO THIS THING!
Looks like she made it to the wreck.\nI wonder if she'll come back with a\nhaul the size of the others?
Hmm. There's something strange here.\nWait, look at those teeth...
Oh no! Look at all that splashing!\nI think it's attacking her!
Hang on, Celliera! We'll save you!
Guys, look at the size of this thing!
I can't believe she caught a shark\nwith her bare hands...
Oh, I am SO sorry, Celliera!\nMy fortune nearly got you killed!

Sure, it caught me off guard when it
attacked, but our underwater struggle
was the best training I've had in days!
Maybe WEEKS!
By the way, what parts of this are tasty?
